This paper deals with programming language techniques for incremental computation, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a refinement type and effect system, which is related to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses efficient representations of incremental sequences and sets, which are data structures that fall under the data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories.
